I had a sampler platter of sorts with some pulled pork, this taro leaf mixture, and lau lau which is the taro leaf-wrapped item. This was advertised as being full of fish, but instead it was 100% pork. So basically the pulled park and taro leaf mixture whose name I have forgotten were a decomposed version of the same components of the lau lau.  Both the pulled pork and the lau lau were painfully salty and greasy. Maybe I got the bottom of the mixing bowl on those. The taro leaf mixture was more edible, but it was sickly sweet. I couldn’t even finish the meal.  The white slab is haupia, but I did not know this at the time. I thought it was a slab of coconut butter, and the meal definitely did not need more oil. So I threw it away. But FYI it is actually the dessert, and it is quite good! (Based on my experience at other restaurants)  I am especially disappointed after hearing good things about this place from multiple locals. Finally, I truly wanted the food to be good because the staff are very nice, but sadly it did not live up to the hype.
